Create version control account on GitHub and using Git commands to
create a repository Create any application and push your code to GitHub.


ChatGPT said:
Sure! Here's a step-by-step guide to:

✅ Create a GitHub account

✅ Create a repository

✅ Use Git commands to push your project (like the registration app above)

🧑‍💻 Step 1: Create a GitHub Account
Go to https://github.com

Click Sign Up

Fill in username, email, password

Verify email and complete signup

📦 Step 2: Create a New Repository on GitHub
After login, click the “+” icon in the top-right

Select “New repository”

Enter:

Repository name: registration-app (or anything)

Description: Simple User Registration App using JS & LocalStorage

Choose: Public (or Private if you prefer)

Click Create repository

🖥️ Step 3: Setup Git Locally on Vagrant/Ubuntu
Open your terminal inside Vagrant:

bash
Copy
Edit
# Install Git if not installed
sudo apt update
sudo apt install git

# Set up your identity (only once)
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your-email@example.com"
🛠️ Step 4: Initialize Git & Push Code
Navigate to the folder where your app files are located:

bash
Copy
Edit
cd /var/www/html
mkdir registration-app
cd registration-app

# Copy your files into this folder (or create new ones)
# For example:
nano index.html
nano script.js
nano users.html
Then run these Git commands:

bash
Copy
Edit
# Initialize Git
git init

# Add your files
git add .

# Commit the changes
git commit -m "Initial commit of user registration app"

# Link to your GitHub repository (replace the URL)
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/registration-app.git

# Push code to GitHub
git push -u origin master
⚠️ Replace your-username and repository URL with your actual GitHub info.

If you're using HTTPS, Git will prompt for your GitHub username and personal access token (instead of password).
Create a token here: https://github.com/settings/tokens

✅ You’re Done!
You can now see your project live at:
https://github.com/your-username/registration-app

